=Chinese Art=

==Literature==
===Monographs===
* Sherman E. Lee: China, 5000 years : innovation and transformation in the arts. New York : Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum, 1998 [[@http://archive.org/download/china5000yearsin00lees/china5000yearsin00lees.pdf|pdf]] 
* Martin J. Powers: Pattern and Person. Ornament, Society and Self in Classical China. Cambridge and London: Harvard University Press, 2006.
===Articles===
* Lydia Haustein: Alle unter einem Himmel. NZZ Samstag, 5. Mai. [[@http://www.nzz.ch/aktuell/feuilleton/kunst_architektur/alle-unter-einem-himmel-1.16751822|link]] 
* Robert Poor: THE CIRCLE AND THE SQUARE: MEASURE AND RITUAL IN ANCIENT CHINA. Monumenta Serica, Vol. 43, (1995), pp. 159-21
* Martin J. Powers: THE FIGURE IN THE CARPET: REFLECTIONS ON THE DISCOURSE OF ORNAMENT IN ZHOU CHINA. Monumenta Serica. Vol. 43, (1995), pp. 211-233
===Indices===
* Robert H. Felsing:  Index to the Meishu congshu 美術叢書 , Huashi congshu 畫史叢書 , Yishu congbian 藝術叢編. University of Oregon, Knight Library 1991 [[@http://purl.library.uoregon.edu/e-asia/ebooks/read/meishu.pdf|pdf]] 
